The paper discusses the development of Artificial General Intelligence (AGI) and its potential safety concerns, which are primarily related to artificial intelligence (AI) and robotics (RO). Therefore, cs.AI and cs.RO are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also covers recent research on solving safety problems, which falls under the category of machine learning (LG). Additionally, the paper discusses public policy on AGI, which could be categorized under computer security and cryptography (CR) and software engineering (SE).
